				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">The Rules of Molto Espressivo.<a name="35054"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 16 04 2:27 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1.  Real life cash and Molto Espressivo do not mix.  
<br />

<br />
Use of real life cash to purchase characters, equipment, PLing services, h4wt cyb0rz, in-game money, Adventure points, or anything else in the EQ-world will not be tolerated.
<br />

<br />

<br />
2.  Molto Espressivo is Bard-only.  
<br />

<br />
If you have a friend or a 2nd-box character that wants in, they can join our sister guild, Nellarmonia.  Their web page is http://www.nellarmonia.com/home.html
<br />

<br />

<br />
3.  Bards of Molto Espressivo do not sell their gear.  They hand it down at guild events.  
<br />

<br />
We're all bards, and there are hardly any NO-DROP items on our server, so it works out pretty well this way.  We only pass down gear at our guild events, except for equipping squeakers with standard newby gear.  If you have something that no-one wants, then you're free to pawn it.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
4.  Don't be a dick.  
<br />

<br />
This is a catch-all.  There are a couple of particulars to mention here.  Don't brag about your Vex Thal gear by linking it in channel when some squeaker asks what they should look for in the bazaar.  Be sensitive to the fact that we don't all play at the same level, and what might be easy for you might be very difficult for others.  If a group wipes, try to figure out what went wrong and fix it, rather than casting blame.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=601903">Feroce</a> <br> 
Battle Bard, Grandmaster Smith, and Tradeskill Officer of Molto Espressivo, the All-Bard Guild of Firiona Vie</span></td>
